\paragraph*{{\bfseries\sffamily ADD} Point out points marked with N² in Figure 5.}
\label{sec-7-3-1-1}
\paragraph*{{\bfseries\sffamily ADD} Agrees well with scaling.}
\label{sec-7-3-1-2}
\paragraph*{Text}
\label{sec-7-3-1-3}
We specify the background density profile using
\[ N^2 = N_0^2 \exp{(-z/H_N)} \]
where $N_0$ is the maximum $N^2$ value and $H_N$ is a vertical decay scale. We impose a minimum value of $N=\SI{1e-3}{1/s}$. The vertical modes for this $N^2$ profile over a flat bottom  are estimated using the algorithm in \citet{Chelton1998}. For these runs, the eddies have a horizontal length scale equal to the first mode baroclinic radius and vertical scale equal to the depth of the zero-crossing of the first baroclinic mode
